Merge pull request #107 from BendingSpoons/feature/side-effect-refactor

Side effects refactor
Fix issue when animating node descriptions with children

Refactor SideEffectDependencyContainer

This commit adds a new way to handle dependency container.

The most important change is that the dependency container is not instantiated anymore on each side effect. While the purpose of preventing the state in the container, it leads to very weird and hard to maintein usages of the managers (in the best case, singletons) to work with the Apple framework. This defeats entirely the purpose of the instantiation every time and therefore we decided to remove it.

The second big change is that the container doesnt receive the state anymore. We have realized that managers/dependencies shouldnt have access to the state but they should use actions.

Third and last change is the class enforcement of the container. We have realized that without creating the container every time we may have issues with structs. In order to prevent these issues, we now enforce that the contains should be a class

Add previousState in side effects

This commits completes the work of the previous commit. It adds the state before the updateState. In this way the side effect has all the information that are needed to properly take actions

Execute side effects after the update state

As discussed internally it seems that it is better to run the side effects after the updateState. By moving the side effects after the updateState we are able to have the updatedState when running custom logic in the sideEffects.

This commit alone is not enough to solve the issues we are facing since we have basically lost the previous state. Following commits will solve also this problem
